==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Effervescency
<hw>Ef`fer*ves"cen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>effervescence</ets>.]</ety> <def>A kind of natural ebullition;
that commotion of a fluid which takes place when some part of the mass
flies off in a gaseous form, producing innumerable small bubbles;
<as>as, the <ex>effervescence</ex> of a carbonate with citric
acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effervescent</ent>⟦br⟧
